<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="I" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Inordinate" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Inordinate,</orth> improper, immoderate: <cit><quote>nothing in him seemed i.</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 94" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 94</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>such i. and low desires,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.2.12" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A III, 2, 12</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>every i. cup is unblessed,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 2.3.311" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. II, 3, 311</bibl></cit> (Q<hi rend="sub">1</hi> <emph>unordinate</emph>).
